7bebbd87-be9b-587e-9cc2-f2804b9a1fbe,tg:rubgr:1949,e73_Descriptions,,id.desc,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,"[recto] Tolnay. Newly Discovered Miniatures by Pieter Bruegel the Elder, Burl. Mag., CVII, 1965, p. 110f. Towneley Lectionarium. Fig. 3 Stormy Harbour  4 x 7cm from Towneley Lectionary, f° 23, Public Libray, New York. Here sky treatment like in Dr. Becker's painting. p. 110 The relationship of this early miniature to Bruegel's work is obvious. It is sufficient to refer to its close connection with the earliest known painting by the master, the Landscape with Sailing Boats and a Burning Town, in a private collection (3) F. GROSSMANN, The Paintings of P. Bruegel the Elder, N° 1 (1955), cat.n° 1, in which the two sailing ships in the centre foreground are almost identical with the two in the left foreground p. 113 of the tiny Bruegel miniature, p. 113 Miniature done in Rome 1553; M. Levi d'Ancona, Illuminati by Clovio Lost & Found, Gaz.B.Arts, 1950, p. 55 very detailed study of Towneley Lectionarium. She dates the Last Judgment miniature hypothetical after 1561; [verso] Webster Smith in MA thesis, Inst. of Fine Arts, New York Univ. (1951) dated the Lectionary between 1550 & 1560.",descriptive note,Nederlands,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,

column4: <content>[recto] Tolnay. Newly Discovered Miniatures by Pieter Bruegel the Elder, Burl. Mag., CVII, 1965, p. 110f. Towneley Lectionarium. Fig. 3 Stormy Harbour  4 x 7cm from Towneley Lectionary, f° 23, Public Libray, New York. Here sky treatment like in Dr. Becker's painting. p. 110 The relationship of this early miniature to Bruegel's work is obvious. It is sufficient to refer to its close connection with the earliest known painting by the master, the Landscape with Sailing Boats and a Burning Town, in a private collection (3) F. GROSSMANN, The Paintings of P. Bruegel the Elder, N° 1 (1955), cat.n° 1, in which the two sailing ships in the centre foreground are almost identical with the two in the left foreground p. 113 of the tiny Bruegel miniature, p. 113 Miniature done in Rome 1553; M. Levi d'Ancona, Illuminati by Clovio Lost & Found, Gaz.B.Arts, 1950, p. 55 very detailed study of Towneley Lectionarium. She dates the Last Judgment miniature hypothetical after 1561; [verso] Webster Smith in MA thesis, Inst. of Fine Arts, New York Univ. (1951) dated the Lectionary between 1550 & 1560.</content>
<object.title>Landscape with Sailing Boats and a Burning Town</object.title>
